Kaitlyn joined the Workplace Relations & Safety team in 2011 and represents clients in a diverse range of employment and industrial matters.  Her areas of expertise include:

• statutory and common law employment agreements;
• developing enforceable restraint of trade provisions and seeking injunctive relief for clients;
• modern award  and enterprise agreement interpretation;
• conducting complex and sensitive workplace investigations; 
• providing advice relating to termination of employment and organisational restructures;
• industrial relations litigation, strategy and advice; and
• general employment law advice and litigation.

Kaitlyn's significant matters include acting for the Director of the Fair Work Building Industry Inspectorate in a Federal Court civil penalty prosecution against the CFMEU and the CFMEU Victorian Branch President alleging numerous breaches of the Fair Work Act 2009 (Cth) and acting for two national clients in separate Supreme Court proceedings against two former employees to seek interlocutory injunctions, including successfully obtaining and executing an Anton Piller order.

Kaitlyn acted for Peninsula Support Services in the landmark decision of a Full Bench of the Commission  which established the temporal scope of the new anti-bullying jurisdiction such that workers who have been bullied prior to 1 January 2014 can seek orders aimed at preventing bullying from continuing or reoccurring (Kathleen McInnes).  She also acted in the landmark Mammoet case before the High Court of Australia regarding the prohibition on making payments to employees during protected industrial action under the Fair Work Act 2009 (Cth) (Construction, Mining, Forestry & Energy Union v Mammoet Australia).

In October 2016, Kaitlyn became a Law Institute of Victoria Accredited Specialist in Workplace Relations, having successfully completed a rigorous assessment process testing experience, technical knowledge, writing and practical advocacy skills.

general.description:
Gavin specialises in professional indemnity and product recall claims, but has significant experience across a number of areas.  

Gavin has acted for local insurers and London underwriters, has practised in Victoria and New South Wales and has conducted litigation in various Australian courts and jurisdictions, including the Federal Court of Australia, the Supreme Court of Victoria and the Court of Appeal.  

Gavin works closely with senior management within our insurer clients to ensure our team provides the best possible support, including presenting on relevant legal developments.  He handles claims involving co-insurers and third party claims handlers and is adept and managing such relationships.  He is focused on ensuring brokers and insureds feel supported and regularly updated and works to develop relationships of trust with both.  Gavin has previously worked for both an international insurer and a local insurer on secondment, providing him with insights into the commercial drivers and internal processes of both.

Gavin has strong experience and connections within the market and is a committee member with APIG Victoria.  

Gavin's areas of expertise include:

- professional indemnity, including accountants, auditors, financial services professionals, real estate professionals, tax professionals and others;
- product recall, including the automotive sector, chemicals/herbicides and others;
investigations and inquiries, including Royal Commissions and liquidator's examinations;
- defamation;
- crime and fidelity claims;
- employment practices liability, including discrimination, general protections and unfair dismissal;
- OHS claims and investigations;
- intellectual property, in particular copyright;
- incorporated associations, such as cultural or sporting organisations;
- property damage;
- public liability.

Gavin joined Lander & Rogers in 2005 and was admitted to practice in 2006.

