At the commencement of 2014 Linda Rayment and Claire Walczak developed a Human Trafficking Taskforce as part of their then role as the co-chairs of the LIV Young Lawyers Community Issues Committee (CIC) for passionate young lawyers wishing to make a difference in human trafficking in Australia. 

 Various speakers have presented at the Taskforce meetings, including:
• Kelly Hinton, Project Respect; 
• Fiona McLeod SC; 
• Jennifer Burn, Anti-Slavery Australia;
• Senior Sergeant Marilyn Ross, Sex Industry Coordination Unit, Victoria Police;
• Superintendent John Tanti, National Coordinator, Crime Operations, AFP; and
• Ann Clark, National Program Coordinator, Support for Trafficked People Program.


 The Human Trafficking Taskforce is now independent of the CIC and is establishing a volunteer legal clinic in Melbourne to assist victims of human trafficking.

 Please contact Linda at linda@nicholeslaw.com.au if you are interested in joining the taskforce.
